cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper focuses on dialog act identification and segmentation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning and deep learning techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.AI a likely category as well. The use of deep learning models such as bidirectional LSTM also suggests that cs.LG (Learning) could be a relevant category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) as it involves identifying functional segments in conversations, which could be useful for search engines and recommendation systems, making cs.IR a possible category. Finally, the paper involves data processing and analysis, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound).
